'''Lukáš Provod''' (born 23 October 1996) is a Czech professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)#Winger|left winger]] for [[Czech First League]] club [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]] and the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]].

==Life==
Provod was born and raised in [[Plzeň]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Soukup|first=Zdeněk|title=Většina kluků ani neví, že jsem z Plzně, usmál se Provod po návratu domů|url=https://plzensky.denik.cz/fotbal-prvni-liga/vetsina-kluku-ani-nevi-ze-jsem-z-plzne-usmal-se-provod-po-navratu-domu-20220404.html|work=Deník.cz|language=cs|date=4 April 2022|access-date=9 February 2026}}</ref>

==Club career==
Provod played in the [[Bohemian Football League]] in the 2015–16 season, representing [[TJ Jiskra Domažlice|Domažlice]], who were operating as a [[farm team]] for his parent club [[FC Viktoria Plzeň|Viktoria Plzeň]]. He joined [[FK Baník Sokolov|Baník Sokolov]] on a season-long loan for the 2016–17 season. He played in all of his team's first five league matches in the [[Czech National Football League]], scoring in the away game against [[FK Pardubice|Pardubice]]. Provod also represented Sokolov in the [[Czech Cup]], scoring in the 2–1 second round loss against [[SK Zápy|Zápy]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Ivo|last=Vymětalík|title=Chvála útočníka Provoda ze Sokolova: Jsem naprosto se vším spokojen|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/domaci-souteze/fotbal-sokolov-provod.A160910_2272301_fot_dsouteze_tof|website=[[Mladá fronta Dnes]]|location=Prague|publisher=[[Mafra (company)|Mafra]]|date=10 September 2016|access-date=10 May 2025|language=cs}}</ref>

Provod joined [[SK Dynamo České Budějovice|České Budějovice]] for the second half of the [[2018–19 Czech National Football League]], celebrating the second-tier title and promotion to the [[Czech First League]] with the club at the end of the season.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Ortman |first1=Bohumil |title=Do ligy se nepostupuje každý den, usmíval se Provod |url=https://ceskobudejovicky.denik.cz/fotbal-druha-liga/do-ligy-se-nepostupuje-kazdy-den-usmival-se-provod-20190523.html |website=[[Deník]] |access-date=10 May 2025 |language=cs |date=23 May 2019}}</ref>

On 3 September 2019, [[SK Slavia Prague|Slavia Prague]] confirmed that Provod had arrived on loan from [[FC Viktoria Plzeň|Viktoria Plzeň]] for the remainder of the calendar year, and signed a deal for a permanent transfer afterwards.<ref>{{Cite web|title=New signing: Lukáš Provod|url=https://en.slavia.cz/clanek.asp?id=New-signing-Lukas-Provod-443|website=Slavia Prague|date=3 September 2019|access-date=10 May 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Provod received his first call-up by coach [[Jaroslav Šilhavý]] for [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League B]] matches against [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]] and [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Do reprezentace míří další slávisté, Šilhavý povolal i Hovorku s Provodem|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/reprezentace/ceske-slovensko-liga-narodu-nominace-reprezentace-lukas-provod-david-hovorka-michael-krmencik.A200831_105923_fot_reprez_min|website=[[Mladá fronta Dnes]]|location=Prague|publisher=[[Mafra (company)|Mafra]]|date=31 August 2020|access-date=28 March 2021|language=cs}}</ref> He debuted in the former match on 4 September 2020, which the Czech Republic won 3–1.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Slovensko 1–3 Česko|trans-title=Slovakia 1–3 Czech Republic|url=https://isport.blesk.cz/fotbal/liga-narodu-uefa-liga-narodu-uefa-liga-b-2020-2021/slovensko-cesko/online-prenos?match=299144|website=[[Blesk]]|agency=[[Czech News Center]]|date=4 September 2020|access-date=28 March 2021|language=cs|quote=Lukáš Provod byl poprvé po svém příchodu na trávník v akci, přes dva protihráče dokonce dokázal odcentrovat, ale ve vápnu tentokrát dobře pokryla prostor slovenská obrana|trans-quote=Lukáš Provod was in action for the first time after his arrival on the pitch. He even managed to cross over two opponents, but this time, the Slovak defense covered the space well in the penalty area.}}</ref>

On 27 March 2021, Provod scored his first senior international goal in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification]] match against [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Jiří|last=Cihák|title=Provodovo senzační jaro. Gól proti Belgii? Mohly být dva, tak snad příště, řekl|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/reprezentace/lukas-provod-cesko-belgie.A210327_231216_fot_reprez_jic?zdroj=vykuk_obecny|website=Mladá fronta Dnes|location=Prague|publisher=Mafra|date=27 March 2021|access-date=28 March 2021|language=cs}}</ref> He was not included in the [[UEFA Euro 2020]] squad due to a serious knee injury.<ref>{{Cite news|title=V nominaci reprezentace na ME chybí Dočkal, Šilhavý čeká na Kúdelu|url=https://www.eurofotbal.cz/clanky/v-nominaci-reprezentace-na-me-chybi-dockal-silhavy-ceka-na-kudelu-502583/|url-status=dead|date=25 May 2021|access-date=19 July 2021|website=Eurofotbal|language=cs|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210606080107/https://www.eurofotbal.cz/clanky/v-nominaci-reprezentace-na-me-chybi-dockal-silhavy-ceka-na-kudelu-502583/|archive-date=6 June 2021}}</ref>

On 28 May 2024, Provod was selected in the 26-man squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Nominace reprezentace na přípravný kemp před Euro 2024|trans-title=National team nominations for the preparatory camp before Euro 2024|url=https://www.fotbal.cz/repre/nominace/nominace/836|publisher=[[Czech Football Association]]|date=28 May 2024|language=cs|access-date=10 May 2025}}</ref> The same year on 18 June, he scored his country's first goal of the tournament during their opening match against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]], which ended in a 2–1 defeat.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Ondřej|last=Nováček|title=Provod: Kdyby nás někde vybagovali nebo to trefili ze třiceti metrů... Bolí to extrémně|url=https://sport.ceskatelevize.cz/clanek/fotbal/me/me-2024/provod-kdyby-nas-nekde-vybagovali-nebo-to-trefili-ze-triceti-metru-boli-to-extremne/6671fd5661d8d47534af0943|website=[[ČT Sport]]|publisher=[[Czech Television]]|date=18 June 2024|language=cs|access-date=10 May 2025}}</ref>

